    <h1 style="text-align:center;">Medicare Coverage at Ashley Regional Medical Center — Vernal, Utah</h1>
    
        <p>Ashley Regional Medical Center is a primary healthcare facility for Vernal and the eastern Uintah Basin. Whether your Medicare plan covers care at Ashley Regional depends on your coverage type.</p>

        <h2>Original Medicare at Ashley Regional</h2>
        <p>Ashley Regional Medical Center accepts Original Medicare (Part A and Part B). If you have Original Medicare — whether standalone or paired with Medigap — you can receive covered services at Ashley Regional with standard Medicare cost-sharing. Part A covers inpatient hospital stays, and Part B covers outpatient services, emergency room visits, lab work, and imaging.</p>

        <h2>Medicare Advantage Plans and Ashley Regional</h2>
        <p>Not all Medicare Advantage plans include Ashley Regional in their network. HMO plans require in-network hospital use (except emergencies), so it is essential to verify Ashley Regional is listed before enrolling. PPO plans cover out-of-network hospitals but at higher costs. We check Ashley Regional's participation in every plan we compare for Vernal residents.</p>

        <h2>Services Available at Ashley Regional</h2>
        <p>Ashley Regional offers emergency care, inpatient hospital stays, surgical services, imaging and radiology, laboratory services, rehabilitation and therapy, and outpatient services. Medicare coverage for each service depends on medical necessity and your specific plan. Pre-authorization may be required for some procedures under Medicare Advantage plans.</p>

        <h2>Emergency Care Is Always Covered</h2>
        <p>Regardless of your Medicare plan type, emergency care at Ashley Regional is covered at in-network rates. Federal law requires Medicare plans to cover genuine emergencies at any hospital. You should never avoid the ER due to network concerns in a true emergency.</p>

        <h2>Verifying Your Coverage</h2>
        <p>Before scheduling non-emergency care, confirm your plan covers Ashley Regional. We handle this verification as part of our free plan comparison service. Call <a href="tel:+14352195120">435-219-5120</a> to confirm your coverage.</p>

